Store elements of first array in HashSet

Check second array elements one by one

If found â†’ common element exists

ðŸ’» Code
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] a = {1, 2, 3, 4};
        int[] b = {5, 6, 3, 8};

        HashSet<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();

        for (int x : a) {
            set.add(x);
        }

        boolean found = false;

        for (int y : b) {
            if (set.contains(y)) {
                found = true;
                break;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(found);
    }
}


ðŸ§  Meaning:
If any number appears in both arrays â†’ true
